  {{#freestyle-section name="Structure" as |section|}}
    {{#section.subsection name="Card"}}
      {{#freestyle-usage "xui-card" title="Example"}}
        <div class="xui-display-flex xui-black-lighten-1-bg xui-padding-two xui-align-flex-start">
          {{#xui-card draggable=true
            square=true
            width="25%"
            heightRatio=1
            selected=true}}
            <div class="xui-card__before-img">
              <span class="xui-card__text" contenteditable="true">Some Name</span>
            </div>
            <div class="xui-card__img" style={{background-image "//via.placeholder.com/250?text=img"}}></div>
            <div class="xui-card__after-img">
              <div>
                {{svg-jar "thumb-up"}}
              </div>
              <div>
                {{svg-jar "dots-horizontal"}}
              </div>
            </div>
          {{/xui-card}}
          {{#xui-card width="25%" square=false draggable=true}}
            <div class="xui-card__text">
              {{svg-jar "collection"}}
              Some truncated collection name with a long name.
            </div>
          {{/xui-card}}
        </div>
      {{/freestyle-usage}}
      {{#freestyle-note "xui-card--notes"}}
      Cards are normally used within a grid view to showcase assets, folders, or collections.

      Note: You'll most likely want to use cards in a flex container with some item alignment or content justification (see example).

      ### Args
      * `selected (boolean)`: Gives the card a selected state
      * `draggable (boolean)`: Adds the draggable HTML5 attribute
      * `width (string)`: A percentage value describing how much of the parents width the card should span.
      * `square (boolean)`: Gives the card 1:1 dimensions.
      * `heightRatio (number)`: Only applicable for when square=true. Allows for specifying custom height ratio (1:2).
      {{/freestyle-note}}
