    {{#section.subsection name="Menu"}}
      {{#freestyle-usage "menu-click" title="Example"}}
        {{#xui-menu/wrapper as |menu|}}
          {{#menu.trigger}}
            {{svg-jar "dots-horizontal"}}
          {{/menu.trigger}}
          {{#menu.anchor as |items|}}
            {{items.item icon="folder" text="Item 1"}}
            {{items.divider}}
            {{items.item text="Item 2"}}
          {{/menu.anchor}}
        {{/xui-menu/wrapper}}
      {{/freestyle-usage}}
      {{#freestyle-note "menu-click--notes"}}
        A menu that can be opened via click, hover, or right click. Anything passed within {{menu.trigger}} will become the target for opening the menu. Note, menu yields the closure action "openMenu" in case you'd prefer to bring your own trigger.

        ### Wrapper Args
        * `eventType (string)`: Specify the type of trigger (click, mouseEnter, contextMenu)
        * `anchor (string)`: See material surface menu docs for anchor types. Defaults to "BOTTOM_LEFT".
        ### Item Args
        * `text (string)`: Menu item text
        * `icon (string)`: Menu item icon
        * `disabled (boolean)`: Disables menu item (actions will not fire)
        * `hidden (boolean)`: Hides the menu item
        * `keyboard (string)`: Show the keyboard shortcut (if one exists)
        * `action (ClosureAction)`: An action which is fired after clicking the menu.
      {{/freestyle-note}}
    {{/section.subsection}}
